snippet.textDisplay: Kernel driver for anti-cheat for Doom? And so yet another crime of application design has happened. This is one of the reasons why I rarely play AAA titles on PC. If they do this nonsense on console, my PC and data are still safe. Crap like that is yet another avenue for hackers to plant more dangerous malware on a PC and have full access to the system. Plus, I don't trust publishers to 'get it right' and not hamper or crash the system given how rushed and untested much of their software is. Gaming rigs have such a wide variety of hardware and software running on them that it is extremely difficult to build something for the kernel level that won't crash a lot of PCs and this is yet another benefit of consoles where the hardware/software are more consistent.
